apiConstructor.shortdesc: Creates an instance of CloudModelSource with the given name and the download conditions.

apiParam.apiDesc: The name of the model to download. Specify the name you assigned the model when you uploaded it to the Firebase console. Within the same Firebase app, all cloud models should have distinct names.
Indicates whether model updates are enabled.

Subsequent update conditions for the model. If it is null and `enableModelUpdates` is true, the default download conditions are used.

apiValueDetail.apiDesc: Subsequent update conditions for the model. If null is passed to the initializer, the default download conditions are set, but are only used if enableModelUpdates is true.

apiOperation.shortdesc: Appends an input at the next index.

apiParam.apiDesc: Input data for the next index. Input can be ByteArray, or a one-dimensional or multi-dimensional array of Numbers (Number, int, string).

apiOperationDetail.apiDesc: Appends an input at the next index. The index starts from 0 and is incremented each time an input is added.

apiClassifier.shortdesc: Options for a custom model specifying input and output data types and dimensions.

apiOperation.shortdesc: Sets the type and dimensions for the input at a given index.

apiParam.apiDesc: The index of the input to configure.
The element type for the input at a given index.

The array of dimensions for the input at a given index. Each dimension should have an uint value. For example, for a 2 dimensional input with 4 rows and 9 columns, the corresponding dimensions should be provided as an Array containing two Numbers with unsigned integer values, 4 and 9 respectively.

apiOperationDetail.apiDesc: Sets the type and dimensions for the input at a given index.

The array of dimensions for the output at a given index. Each dimension should have an uint value. For example, for a 2 dimensional output with 4 rows and 9 columns, the corresponding dimensions should be provided as an Array containing two Numbers with unsigned integer values, 4 and 9 respectively.
